The paper discusses a technique for coordinated multi-point (CoMP) transmission in future cellular systems, which involves analyzing the average throughput of each user under CoMP and Non-CoMP transmission after taking into account the downlink training overhead. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, since the focus is on transmission mode selection and channel information acquisition, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories.
